-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vkk1665702553651.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vkk1665702553651.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vkk1665702553651.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vkk1665702553651\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Sorting Data in ProcScript\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__sorting_data_in_procscript_56665\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface provides ProcScript instructions for sorting entity occurrences in hitlists and lists created in ProcScript. It is possible to perform multi-level sorting, enabling you to sort by several fields, each with its own sort criteria.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__p_d16781e1_d16782e1_d16783e1\">You can use the following ProcScript instructions for sorting lists such as property lists, ValRep lists, and nested lists of various kinds.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">ProcScript Instructions for Sorting Data</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__1\">\n ProcScript\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mfl1718885236878.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mfl1718885236878.html\" title=\"Set or return the current sequencing rules to apply when sorting strings in entities and lists, or reading occurrences from the hitlist.\">$nlssortorder</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__2\">\n Return or set the current sort ordering rules.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jei1665702553041.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jei1665702553041.html\" title=\"Sort the occurrences in the hitlist for the specified entity.\">sort</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__2\">\n Sort entities on one or more fields.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kes1665702553734.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kes1665702553734.html\" title=\"Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an indexed list of sub-lists.\">sort/list</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__2\">\n Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an indexed list of sublists.\n <p class=\"p\">WHY the distinctions between sort/list and $sortlist?</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kes1665702553734.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kes1665702553734.html\" title=\"Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an indexed list of sub-lists.\">sort/list</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__2\">\n Sort an associative list or an indexed list.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wqe1719856383580.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wqe1719856383580.html\" title=\"Sort an associative list in which the value part of each list item is an indexed list.\">$sortlistid</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1__entry__2\">\n Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an associative list of sublists.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__topic_d12167e1_d12168e1_d12169e1_d12170e1_d12171e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d866952e167\">\n            \n Sort Element and Sort Options\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__p_d16787e1_d16788e1_d16789e1\">When using the ProcScript sorting instructions, you need to specify the data to sort (an entity or a list), and optionally, one or more elements to sort by. For each element, you can specify the sort options. Although the exact syntax of ProcScript statements and functions is different, the syntax for specifying the sort options is the same:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__p_d16790e1_d16791e1_d16792e1\">{<var class=\"keyword varname\">ElementToSortBy</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOrder</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Unique</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Type</var> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>\n</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ElementToSortBy</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SortOrder</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Unique</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Type</var>} }</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__p_d16793e1_d16794e1_d16795e1\">The <var class=\"keyword varname\">ElementToSortBy</var> and sort options are specified as a comma-separated or GOLD ; (<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>) separated list. All sort options are optional. After the <var class=\"keyword varname\">ElementToSortBy</var>, they can be defined in any order.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__li_d7862e1_d7863e1_d7864e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ElementToSortBy</var>—entity field (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sort</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sort/e</span> only), list item, or sublist item on which to sort.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Sort Options</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__1\">Sort Option</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">Valid Values</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Order</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ascending</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">A</code>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">descending</code> | <span class=\"keyword option\">D</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort order</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Unique</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unique</code> |\n\t\t\t\t <code class=\"ph codeph\">U</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Keep only unique items; discard duplicates.\n                           <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eds1665702557855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html#eds1665702557855__section_jdk_dkx_tcc\">Example: Removing Items with Duplicate Values</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"19\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Type</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Determines how sorting is performed by\n\t\t\t\t specifying the locale, case sensitivity, level, or data type. If not specified, the default is \n\t\t\t\t <span class=\"keyword option\">nlslocale</span>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">nlslocale</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">NLS</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort as a string using the value of\n\t\t\t\t <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$nlssortorder</span>. If this is not set, the value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$nlslocale</span> is\n\t\t\t\t used. If this is not set, a binary sort is performed. \n                     <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jvl1665702552585.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvl1665702552585.html\" title=\"You can sort data in ProcScript using several ProcScript statements and functions. The default sort order is determined by the data type of the data and the values of NLS settings.\">Sorting Based on Locale</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CaseSensitive</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">CS</code> |\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">classic</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort as a case-sensitive string, ignoring\n\t\t\t\t locale-based sorting conventions.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CaseInsensitive</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">CI</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort as a case-insensitive string, using\n\t\t\t\t the 1-to-1 character matching for Unicode uppercase and lowercase rules. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">level</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort data as level ID\n                        (<var class=\"keyword varname\">n.n.n</var>), so that <code class=\"ph codeph\">9.2</code> is sorted before\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">10.1</code>. <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eds1665702557855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html#eds1665702557855__section_jl3_tjx_tcc\">Example: Sorting by Hierarchical Level</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2 vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__note_w3194ab1b5b7c11b3b9c15b1b1_w3195ab1b5b7c11b3b9c15b1_w3196ab1b5b7c11b3b9c15_w3197ab1b5b7c11b3b9_w3198ab1b5b7c11b3_w3199ab1b5b7c11_w3200ab1b5b7_w3201ab1b5_w3202ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When specifying the following sort\n      options, it is assumed the data is in a format that can be interpreted as the specified data\n      type. <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eds1665702557855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html#eds1665702557855__section_p55_wjx_tcc\">Example: Sorting Using Data Type</a>.</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Numeric</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Numeric</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Float</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Float</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Boolean</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Boolean</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Date</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Date</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Time</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\"> Sort data as Time</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2 vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__note_w3203ab1b5b7c11b3b9c27b1b1_w3204ab1b5b7c11b3b9c27b1_w3205ab1b5b7c11b3b9c27_w3206ab1b5b7c11b3b9_w3207ab1b5b7c11b3_w3208ab1b5b7c11_w3209ab1b5b7_w3210ab1b5_w3211ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When specifying the following sort options, Uniface converts the data to the specified data type before sorting:</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$number</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort Data as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$number</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$float</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort Data as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$float</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$boolean</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort Data as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$boolean</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$date</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort Data as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$date</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$time</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort Data as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$clock</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$datim</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort Data as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$datim</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$string</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vkk1665702553651__table_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1__entry__3\">Sort Data as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vkk1665702553651__p_d16802e1_d16803e1_d16804e1\">For examples demonstrating how you can use the sort\n            options to control sorting behavior, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eds1665702557855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html\" title=\"The following examples demonstrate how you can use the sort options to control sorting behavior.\">Using Sort Options</a>. For examples\n            of list sorting, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qwg1665702557778.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwg1665702557778.html\" title=\"The ProcScript commands sort/list, $sortlist, and $sortlistid enable you to sort all kinds of lists, including indexed lists (flat lists), associative lists (such as property lists and ValRep lists), and nested lists (such as those used in tree widgets).\">Sorting Lists and Sublists</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ayl1665702554178.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Lists and Sublists</a><p>A list is a group of related items homogeneous items collected into a single unit, the list. Every item in a list is assumed to have the same structure.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533056\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533056\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Sorting Data in ProcScript Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Sorting Data in ProcScript Uniface provides ProcScript instructions for sorting entity occurrences in hitlists and lists created in ProcScript. It is possible to perform multi-level sorting, enabling you to sort by several fields, each with its own sort criteria. You can use the following ProcScript instructions for sorting lists such as property lists, ValRep lists, and nested lists of various kinds. Table 1. ProcScript Instructions for Sorting Data ProcScript Description $nlssortorder Return or set the current sort ordering rules. sort Sort entities on one or more fields. sort/list Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an indexed list of sublists. WHY the distinctions between sort/list and $sortlist? sort/list Sort an associative list or an indexed list. $sortlistid Sort an associative list, an indexed list, or an associative list of sublists. Sort Element and Sort Options When using the ProcScript sorting instructions, you need to specify the data to sort (an entity or a list), and optionally, one or more elements to sort by. For each element, you can specify the sort options. Although the exact syntax of ProcScript statements and functions is different, the syntax for specifying the sort options is the same: { ElementToSortBy : SortOrder Unique Type { ; ElementToSortBy : SortOrder Unique Type } } The ElementToSortBy and sort options are specified as a comma-separated or GOLD ; ( ; ) separated list. All sort options are optional. After the ElementToSortBy , they can be defined in any order. ElementToSortBy —entity field ( sort and sort/e only), list item, or sublist item on which to sort. Table 2. Sort Options Sort Option Valid Values Meaning Order ascending | A descending | D Sort order Unique unique | U Keep only unique items; discard duplicates. Example: Removing Items with Duplicate Values Type Determines how sorting is performed by specifying the locale, case sensitivity, level, or data type. If not specified, the default is nlslocale . nlslocale | NLS Sort as a string using the value of $nlssortorder . If this is not set, the value of $nlslocale is used. If this is not set, a binary sort is performed. Sorting Based on Locale CaseSensitive | CS | classic Sort as a case-sensitive string, ignoring locale-based sorting conventions. CaseInsensitive | CI Sort as a case-insensitive string, using the 1-to-1 character matching for Unicode uppercase and lowercase rules. level Sort data as level ID ( n.n.n ), so that 9.2 is sorted before 10.1 . Example: Sorting by Hierarchical Level Note: When specifying the following sort options, it is assumed the data is in a format that can be interpreted as the specified data type. Example: Sorting Using Data Type . Numeric Sort data as Numeric Float Sort data as Float Boolean Sort data as Boolean Date Sort data as Date Time Sort data as Time Note: When specifying the following sort options, Uniface converts the data to the specified data type before sorting: $number Sort Data as $number ( String ) $float Sort Data as $float ( String ) $boolean Sort Data as $boolean ( String ) $date Sort Data as $date ( String ) $time Sort Data as $clock ( String ) $datim Sort Data as $datim ( String ) $string Sort Data as $string ( String ) For examples demonstrating how you can use the sort options to control sorting behavior, see Using Sort Options . For examples of list sorting, see Sorting Lists and Sublists . Related Links Lists and Sublists A list is a group of related items homogeneous items collected into a single unit, the list. Every item in a list is assumed to have the same structure. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}